cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the analysis of language and location metadata in Twitter data, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and social media analysis. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of automated methods for language identification, which falls under the domain of machine learning and information retrieval, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper also touches upon the challenges of working with spatial and linguistic contexts, which falls under the domain of computational geography, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible sub-category.
